<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573483>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—Adult male Bos gaurus with conspicuous dorsal ridge and dewlaps from Nagarahole Tiger Reserve, southern India. Used with permission of the photographer K.Varma (http://www.http://kalyanvarma.net)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573483/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573485>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Adult female Bos gaurus with typical brown pelage and smooth, spiral-shaped horns from BR Hills, southern India. Used with permission of the photographer K. Varma (http://www.http://kalyanvarma.net)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573485/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573489>
    dc:description "Fig. 4.—Age-specific differences in the size and shape of the head and horns, and the black:white ratio on horns of (a) female and (b) male Bos gaurus. (Reprinted from F. S. Ahrestani [2009] Ph.D. dissertation titled “Asian Eden: large herbivore ecology in India”)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573489/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573487>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Differences in thickness, shape, and curvature of horns, and thickness of neck between female and male Bos gaurus from Mysore Zoo, southern India. Photographer F. S. Ahrestani." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573487/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573491>
    dc:description "Fig. 5.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of skull and lateral view of mandible of adult male Bos gaurus (American Museum of Natural History, New York, [AMNH] specimen 54468). Greatest length of skull is 683 mm. Photographer F. S. Ahrestani." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573491/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573495>
    dc:description "Fig. 6.—Distribution of Bos gaurus endemic to southern and southeastern Asia. Map redrawn from International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources Redlist with modifications and courtesy of Srinivas Vaidyanathan, Foundation for Ecological Research, Advocacy and Learning, Puducherry, India." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573495/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573499>
    dc:description "Fig. 7.—Bos gaurus herd with adult females and calves from Bandipur Tiger Reserve, southern India. Used with permission of the photographer M. N. Naveen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573499/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4573503>
    dc:description "Fig. 8.—Two (3- and 6-year-old) captive male Bos gaurus sparring in Mysore Zoo, southern India. Photographer F. S. Ahrestani." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573503/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

